WEBVTT

00:01.542 --> 00:03.624
PREVIOUSLY ON "REVENGE"...

00:03.624 --> 00:04.715
OH, GOD.

00:04.715 --> 00:06.837
THE CORONER RULED IT
AN ACCIDENT.

00:06.837 --> 00:09.470
THIS DARK CHAPTER IN OUR LIVES
IS FINALLY OVER.

00:09.470 --> 00:11.302
WE CAN MOVE ON.
 I DON'T KNOW IF I CAN.

00:11.302 --> 00:13.054
Emily:
LET HIM GO, NIKO.

00:13.054 --> 00:16.187
HE'S GUILTY OF KILLING MY
FATHER, LYING TO ME ABOUT IT.

00:16.187 --> 00:17.638
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

00:19.100 --> 00:21.142
EMILY, NO!
SHE DOESN'T DESERVE TO DIE.

00:21.142 --> 00:22.443
I'VE BEEN
BLACKING OUT.

00:22.443 --> 00:25.146
GET HELP BEFORE YOU DO
SOMETHING ELSE YOU REGRET.

00:26.237 --> 00:29.029
SO, YOU'RE CONRAD'S
FIRST WIFE?
 WE ALL MAKE MISTAKES,
RIGHT?

00:29.029 --> 00:30.701
THIS HOUSE BELONGS
TO ME.

00:30.701 --> 00:34.205
I OWN THIS PLACE, AND I WANT YOU
OUT BY THE END OF THE WEEK.

00:34.205 --> 00:36.077
JACK, I'M YOUR MOTHER.

00:36.077 --> 00:37.658
WHAT IS GOING ON
WITH YOU, EMS?

00:37.658 --> 00:39.120
BLACKOUTS?

00:39.120 --> 00:41.212
I LASHED OUT AT YOU.
I JEOPARDIZED AIDEN'S LIFE.

00:41.212 --> 00:43.084
I'M STARTING TO GO AFTER
THE WRONG PEOPLE, NOLAN.

00:43.084 --> 00:45.296
[ Voice breaking ]
WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

00:49.930 --> 00:51.762
[ SEAGULLS CRYING ]

00:51.762 --> 00:53.264
Emily:
 WE SPEND OUR LIVES

00:53.264 --> 00:56.847
STRUGGLING TO HOLD ON TO
 THE THINGS WE VALUE MOST...

01:02.603 --> 01:04.605
...TO THE PEOPLE AND THINGS

01:04.605 --> 01:07.608
WE BELIEVE WE COULD
 NEVER EXIST WITHOUT.

01:17.538 --> 01:20.831
BUT OUR MEMORIES
 ARE OFTEN AN ILLUSION...

01:22.253 --> 01:25.206
...PROTECTING A FAR MORE
 DESTRUCTIVE TRUTH.

01:27.208 --> 01:28.709
[ KNIFE CLICKS ]

01:28.709 --> 01:31.472
[ HEART BEATING ]

01:41.142 --> 01:43.814
[ SEAGULLS CRYING ]

01:43.814 --> 01:46.857
Jack: THEY'RE CONSIDERING
AN ALL-CASH OFFER?

01:46.857 --> 01:49.780
DID YOU TELL THEM
THAT I HAVE A LITTLE BOY?

01:53.654 --> 01:55.406
[ SIGHS ] FINE.

01:55.406 --> 01:57.037
WELL...

01:57.037 --> 01:58.789
BYE.

01:58.789 --> 02:01.622
HOUSE HUNTING
IN THIS MARKET'S TOUGH, HUH?

02:01.622 --> 02:05.246
I'M JUST TRYING TO GET ON
WITH MY LIFE.

02:05.246 --> 02:08.419
IS THAT WHY YOU HAVEN'T RETURNED
MY CALLS IN THE PAST THREE DAYS?

02:08.419 --> 02:10.751
JACK, I JUST...

02:13.424 --> 02:15.256
I'D LIKE FOR YOU
TO HEAR ME OUT.

02:32.483 --> 02:34.485
I WONDERED WHY I'D NEVER SEEN
ANY PHOTOS OF ME

02:34.485 --> 02:37.117
AS A NEWBORN WITH MY MOM.
[ SIGHS ]

02:37.117 --> 02:39.240
I SAID GOODBYE AND...

02:39.240 --> 02:42.583
I LEFT YOU WITH YOUR FATHER
A WEEK AFTER...

02:42.583 --> 02:44.415
THAT PICTURE WAS TAKEN.

02:44.415 --> 02:47.668
HE SENT MEMENTOS
OVER THE YEARS --

02:47.668 --> 02:51.672
YOUR ARTWORK
AND SAILING RIBBONS.

02:56.217 --> 02:59.560
HE MADE IT POSSIBLE
TO BEAR BEING AWAY.

03:02.803 --> 03:04.605
I'M GLAD
HE MADE IT EASY.

03:04.605 --> 03:07.187
IT WAS NEVER EASY,
JACK.

03:08.519 --> 03:10.231
AND I...

03:10.231 --> 03:12.152
I CAN'T MAKE UP
FOR THE TIME WE LOST.

03:12.152 --> 03:14.194
SO WHY TRY NOW?

03:15.986 --> 03:17.157
IT'S COMPLICATED.

03:17.157 --> 03:19.490
WELL...

03:19.490 --> 03:23.874
I THINK IT'S BEST IF WE KEEP
OUR LIVES TO OURSELVES.

03:24.955 --> 03:26.957
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

03:37.097 --> 03:40.891
Mickey:
MAN NEVER HAD IT EASY,

03:40.891 --> 03:44.935
AND, SURE,
HE MADE HIS MISTAKES.

03:44.935 --> 03:46.937
BUT HE ALWAYS ROSE ABOVE,

03:46.937 --> 03:50.190
AND WE STOOD BY HIM,
JUST LIKE HE STOOD BY US.

03:50.190 --> 03:51.312
Man: YEAH, HE DID.

03:51.312 --> 03:53.524
SO, HERE'S TO YOU, JIMMY.

03:53.524 --> 03:55.195
TAKEN TOO SOON,

03:55.195 --> 03:57.698
BUT WE KNOW YOU'RE THROWING BACK
WITH SAINT PETER NOW.

03:57.698 --> 03:59.740
CHEERS.
 All: CHEERS!

03:59.740 --> 04:02.363
GUY HAD YOU
ALL FOOLED.

04:02.363 --> 04:05.075
YOU GOT SOMETHING
TO SAY, PAL?

04:07.458 --> 04:09.670
JIMMY BRENNAN
WAS A RAPIST

04:09.670 --> 04:12.423
WHO DESERVES TO BE EXACTLY
WHERE HE IS RIGHT NOW --

04:12.423 --> 04:14.675
ROTTING IN A BOX.
[ SPITS ]

04:25.055 --> 04:27.057
YOU'RE PACKING UP.

04:27.057 --> 04:28.979
GOOD TO SEE YOU KNOW
WHEN TO SURRENDER.

04:30.100 --> 04:32.232
WELL, THAT WORD'S NOT
IN MY VOCABULARY.

04:32.232 --> 04:35.065
THESE ARE SIMPLY PIECES ON LOAN
FOR THE HAMPTONS ART WALK.

04:35.065 --> 04:37.778
I HAVE NO INTENTION
OF GOING ANYWHERE.

04:37.778 --> 04:40.110
YET THIS PROPERTY
BELONGS TO ME.

04:40.110 --> 04:42.573
WELL, THAT IS
A RATHER TENUOUS CLAIM,

04:42.573 --> 04:45.165
AS YOU'VE NEITHER SET FOOT ON
NOR PAID TAXES FOR THIS LAND

04:45.165 --> 04:46.827
IN ALL YOUR YEARS AWAY.

04:46.827 --> 04:49.830
OH, YOUR LAWYER'S ADVISED YOU
TO DENY ME ACCESS

04:49.830 --> 04:52.333
WITH THE CLAIM
OF ABANDONMENT -- CLEVER.

04:52.333 --> 04:53.914
BUT IF HE WERE
REALLY SHARP,

04:53.914 --> 04:55.676
HE'D KNOW THAT
I WAS DEFRAUDED TITLE

04:55.676 --> 04:57.678
SINCE CONRAD
HID OWNERSHIP FROM ME.

04:57.678 --> 05:00.050
DECADES LATER,
YOU'RE STILL THAT MAN'S PAWN.

05:00.050 --> 05:01.762
WHAT I AM, VICTORIA,

05:01.762 --> 05:03.924
IS THE LEGAL OWNER
OF THIS HOUSE,

05:03.924 --> 05:06.096
WHICH I INTEND TO RAZE
TO THE GROUND.

05:06.096 --> 05:08.268
OH, STEVIE,

05:08.268 --> 05:10.060
YOU AND I BOTH KNOW
THE ONLY THING

05:10.060 --> 05:13.313
GUARANTEED
TO CRUMBLE IS YOU.

05:13.313 --> 05:14.895
MM.

05:19.239 --> 05:20.240
[ DOOR OPENS ]

05:20.240 --> 05:22.242
Emily: NOLAN?
 HEY.

05:22.242 --> 05:24.495
GOD. NEXT TIME I AGREE
TO CHAIR AN ART WALK, PLEASE --

05:24.495 --> 05:26.246
IT HAPPENED AGAIN.

05:26.246 --> 05:28.248
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
 WHAT DO YOU THINK?

05:28.248 --> 05:29.540
ONE SECOND,
I'M AT GRAYSON MANOR,

05:29.540 --> 05:31.291
AND THE NEXT, I COME TO
ON MY PORCH WITH THIS.

05:31.291 --> 05:32.623
WHAT THE HELL
DID YOU DO?

05:32.623 --> 05:34.505
DESTROYED
MY FATHER'S CARVING.

05:34.505 --> 05:37.508
AT LEAST
IT WASN'T SOMEONE.
 THIS TIME.

05:38.719 --> 05:42.052
I THOUGHT YOU HAD THESE
BLACKOUTS UNDER CONTROL.
 YEAH, SO DID I.

05:42.052 --> 05:44.054
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

05:45.305 --> 05:47.307
I NEED TO FIGURE
SOMETHING OUT.

05:49.099 --> 05:50.681
EMILY,
MAYBE IT'S TIME --

05:50.681 --> 05:52.352
DON'T TELL ME
TO GO TO A DOCTOR!

05:52.352 --> 05:54.104
ALL RIGHT,
THEN I'LL HELP YOU.

05:54.104 --> 05:55.105
WE'LL LEAVE TOWN.

05:55.105 --> 05:56.737
WE'LL GO ANYWHERE.

05:56.737 --> 05:58.569
NO, I NEED TO FINISH
WHAT I STARTED.

05:58.569 --> 06:02.112
HOW CAN YOU IF YOU CANNOT
EVEN TRUST YOURSELF?

06:02.112 --> 06:05.115
LOOK, FOR STARTERS, WHY
DON'T YOU PUT THE KNIFE DOWN?

06:06.447 --> 06:08.659
YOU CAN'T LET THIS
DESTROY YOU.

06:11.251 --> 06:13.253
I WON'T.

06:14.795 --> 06:15.796
EMS.

06:15.796 --> 06:17.998
EMILY, WAIT.

06:17.998 --> 06:20.631
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?
 WHAT I SHOULD'VE DONE
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

06:22.342 --> 06:33.273
I'M GONNA KILL THEM ALL.

06:36.727 --> 06:39.440
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

06:43.403 --> 06:44.404
I'M ALL RIGHT.

06:44.404 --> 06:45.946
NO, PATRICK,
YOU'RE NOT.

06:45.946 --> 06:48.028
WHY WOULD YOU GO
TO JIMMY'S WAKE?

06:48.028 --> 06:50.030
EXPOSE HIM FOR THE BASTARD
THAT HE WAS.

06:50.030 --> 06:52.292
AND ALLOW YOURSELF TO BE BEATEN
BLOODY BY A BUNCH OF THUGS?

06:52.292 --> 06:54.334
YOU'RE GOING TO
GET YOURSELF KILLED.

06:54.334 --> 06:56.036
WELL,
MAYBE I SHOULD.

06:57.458 --> 06:59.419
YOU DON'T
HONESTLY BELIEVE THAT.

06:59.419 --> 07:01.882
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I BELIEVE ANYMORE.

07:01.882 --> 07:03.924
BELIEVE
THAT I LOVE YOU...

07:03.924 --> 07:07.097
THAT JIMMY GOT WHAT HE DESERVED,
AND THAT WE NEED TO MOVE ON.

07:07.097 --> 07:08.889
DON'T LET YOUR RAGE
CONSUME YOU.

07:11.351 --> 07:13.393
IT MIGHT BE TOO LATE.

07:23.443 --> 07:25.736
WELL, SINCE YOU WON'T
RETURN MY PHONE CALLS,

07:25.736 --> 07:28.278
I FIGURED I'D USE MY
"FIND A FORMER FRIEND" APP.

07:28.278 --> 07:30.240
I'M JUST -- I'M TRYING
TO GET OUT OF TOWN.

07:30.240 --> 07:32.202
BUT I KNOW WHY
YOU'RE STILL HERE.

07:32.202 --> 07:34.034
[ HORN HONKS ]
 EMILY'S IN TROUBLE.

07:34.034 --> 07:35.836
LOOK, SHE ALMOST
HAD ME KILLED,

07:35.836 --> 07:38.038
SO IF YOU'RE LOOKING FOR ME
TO SAVE HER, I PASS.

07:38.038 --> 07:40.080
YOU CAN'T HELP SOMEBODY
WHO DOESN'T WANT IT.

07:40.080 --> 07:41.712
REALLY? BECAUSE
FROM WHAT I REMEMBER,

07:41.712 --> 07:44.294
YOU WERE AN UNFOCUSED DISASTER
WHEN EMILY RESCUED YOUR ASS

07:44.294 --> 07:46.216
AND BROUGHT YOU
TO TAKEDA.

07:46.216 --> 07:50.010
BELIEVE ME, IF HE WERE STILL
ALIVE, I WOULD GO TO HIM.

07:50.010 --> 07:52.092
YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
THAT CAN REACH HER NOW.

07:52.092 --> 07:53.514
NO ONE CAN REACH EMILY.

07:53.514 --> 07:55.475
SHE'S GOT THE STRONGEST WILL
I'VE EVER KNOWN.
 HAD.

07:55.475 --> 07:57.518
SHE'S BROKEN DOWN,
SHE'S OUT OF CONTROL.

07:57.518 --> 07:59.730
SHE SAID SHE'S GOING TO
KILL ALL THE GRAYSONS.

07:59.730 --> 08:01.732
THEN LET HER.
THAT'S WHAT I WOULD'VE DONE.

08:01.732 --> 08:03.734
YOU'RE NOT LISTENING
TO ME.

08:03.734 --> 08:08.158
SHE'S ABOUT TO DO SOMETHING SHE
WILL NOT COME BACK FROM EVER.

08:14.575 --> 08:16.537
I WAS SURPRISED
YOU CALLED.

08:16.537 --> 08:20.460
THE GRAYSONS ARE NOTORIOUS
FOR USING THE SAME OLD FOSSILS.

08:20.460 --> 08:24.545
THOSE PRIVATE INVESTIGATORS
ARE LOYAL TO MY PARENTS.

08:24.545 --> 08:26.717
I WANT
SOMEONE INTERESTED

08:26.717 --> 08:29.509
IN BUILDING A RELATIONSHIP
WITH A NEW REGIME.

08:29.509 --> 08:32.842
THOUGHT YOU JUST NEEDED ME
TAILING SOMEONE.

08:32.842 --> 08:35.475
FOR NOW, I DO.

08:35.475 --> 08:39.188
I ASSUME YOU'RE FAMILIAR
WITH MY WIFE.

08:39.188 --> 08:42.312
SHE DISAPPEARS AT ODD HOURS,
DOESN'T COME HOME...

08:42.312 --> 08:45.405
AND MAY BE CONSPIRING
WITH MY FATHER.

08:45.405 --> 08:47.027
YOU WANT A TAIL
FOR HIM, TOO?

08:47.027 --> 08:48.859
'CAUSE THAT WOULD
REQUIRE EXTRA MANPOWER.

08:48.859 --> 08:50.530
I'VE GOT HIM COVERED.

08:50.530 --> 08:52.452
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

08:52.452 --> 08:55.075
NO, NO, NO.
I DON'T NEED TO THINK ABOUT IT.

08:55.075 --> 08:56.206
MY ANSWER IS NO.

08:58.118 --> 09:01.792
YOU, ON THE OTHER HAND,
I'M GLAD I SAID YES TO.

09:01.792 --> 09:03.714
THESE ARE
THE REPORTS YOU WANTED,

09:03.714 --> 09:06.927
BUT I DIDN'T HAVE ACCESS TO SOME
OF THE FINANCIALS YOU ASKED FOR.

09:06.927 --> 09:08.298
OH, THAT'S ALL RIGHT,
SWEETHEART.

09:08.298 --> 09:09.429
I CAN GET THOSE MYSELF.

09:09.429 --> 09:11.381
WHO WAS THAT
ON THE PHONE?

09:11.381 --> 09:13.513
NO ONE
WHO WOULD INTEREST YOU.

09:13.513 --> 09:15.886
TRY ME.

09:17.017 --> 09:19.890
THAT WAS A REPRESENTATIVE
FROM A HEDGE FUND

09:19.890 --> 09:22.442
INTERESTED IN BUYING
MY STAKE IN VOULEZ

09:22.442 --> 09:24.945
AT AN AMATEURISHLY
INFLATED PRICE.

09:24.945 --> 09:26.947
AND WHY SAY NO?

09:26.947 --> 09:29.319
BECAUSE, MY DEAR,
YOU CAN'T PUT A PRICE TAG

09:29.319 --> 09:31.742
ON WORKING ALONGSIDE
YOUR OWN DAUGHTER.

09:31.742 --> 09:36.156
AND MY INTEREST IN THIS ENDEAVOR
IS JUST STARTING TO PIQUE.

09:36.156 --> 09:38.368
NOW, AS VOULEZ'S EMISSARY
AT TODAY'S ART WALK,

09:38.368 --> 09:42.202
I NEED TO GO HOME AND SLIP
INTO SOMETHING MORE CREATIVE.

09:42.202 --> 09:45.125
DADDY, PLEASE DON'T START
CALLING THE SOUTHFORK HOME.

09:45.125 --> 09:46.967
IT MAKES ME SAD.

09:46.967 --> 09:48.969
OH, REALLY?

09:48.969 --> 09:51.972
WELL, I'M THE HAPPIEST
I'VE BEEN IN AGES.

09:56.426 --> 09:59.179
[ CARD READER BEEPS,
DOOR OPENS ]

10:24.955 --> 10:27.668
[ CARD READER BEEPS,
DOORKNOB TURNS ]

11:08.959 --> 11:11.091
[ CAPSULE SNAPS ]
 [ GASPS ]

11:11.091 --> 11:13.844
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

11:13.844 --> 11:16.096
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?
 DON'T WORRY.
YOU'RE SAFE.

11:16.096 --> 11:17.597
FROM WHO?
 FROM YOURSELF.

11:17.597 --> 11:19.679
ATTEMPTING TO KILL CONRAD
IN HIS SUITE WITH NO COVER,

11:19.679 --> 11:21.061
NO EXIT STRATEGY.

11:21.061 --> 11:22.602
I HAD NO CHOICE.

11:22.602 --> 11:25.515
HOW MANY TIMES HAVE YOU TOLD ME
THAT MURDER IS NOT THE ANSWER?

11:25.515 --> 11:27.107
I'M OUT OF OPTIONS.
UNTIE ME, AIDEN.

11:27.107 --> 11:28.518
YOU'RE DESPERATE.

11:28.518 --> 11:31.151
YOU'RE FLAILING AROUND
IN THE DARK WITHOUT A PLAN.

11:31.151 --> 11:32.863
WHEN YOU WERE SHOT, IT SET
SOMETHING FREE IN YOUR MIND.

11:32.863 --> 11:34.444
IT'S CONSUMING YOU.

11:34.444 --> 11:36.196
AND, WHAT, YOU'RE GONNA
TRY TO SNAP ME OUT OF IT?

11:36.196 --> 11:37.988
I'M GONNA MAKE YOU
DEAL WITH IT.

11:41.161 --> 11:44.785
TAKEDA HAD WAYS OF REACHING
YOUR SUBCONSCIOUS BEFORE.

11:44.785 --> 11:46.376
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

11:51.331 --> 11:53.133
DON'T YOU DARE.

11:53.133 --> 11:54.504
[ GRUNTS ]

11:54.504 --> 11:57.047
AS CHAIR
OF THE CULTURAL ARTS BOARD,

11:57.047 --> 12:00.430
I WANT TO THANK YOU ALL
FOR YOUR PARTICIPATION.

12:00.430 --> 12:04.144
YOU HAVE YOUR ASSIGNMENTS,
SO LET'S HAVE A GREAT EVENT.

12:06.106 --> 12:07.808
I WAS JUST
AT THE MARINA.

12:07.808 --> 12:09.229
IT LOOKS BEAUTIFUL,
NOLAN.

12:09.229 --> 12:10.730
MM.

12:10.730 --> 12:13.653
WORTHY OF HAVING STEFANO LEONE
AS OUR V.I.P. GUEST.

12:13.653 --> 12:15.906
AS ONE OF HIS
ORIGINAL BENEFACTORS,

12:15.906 --> 12:17.617
I THOUGHT
IT WAS ONLY FITTING

12:17.617 --> 12:20.030
TO HAVE THE MASTER GRACE US
WITH HIS PRESENCE.

12:25.455 --> 12:27.707
MM.
JEALOUS, VICKY?

12:27.707 --> 12:29.289
I MEAN, I GUESS
THAT'S THE DIFFERENCE

12:29.289 --> 12:31.872
BETWEEN YOU AND I
IN THE ART WORLD.

12:31.872 --> 12:34.294
YOU COLLECT,
AND I CONNECT.

12:34.294 --> 12:35.545
FRANKLY,
I'M SURPRISED

12:35.545 --> 12:37.297
YOU SHOWED UP
TO THIS MEETING AT ALL.

12:37.297 --> 12:40.680
UNLIKE YOURSELF,
I HAVE LITTLE INTEREST

12:40.680 --> 12:42.682
IN PLAYING DILETTANTE
WITH THESE WOMEN.

12:43.683 --> 12:46.266
I'M HERE TO HAVE A CONVERSATION
WITH YOU ALONE.

12:46.266 --> 12:47.687
[ SCOFFS ]

12:47.687 --> 12:50.981
WELL, HANG ON A SEC WHILE I HIDE
ALL THE BLUNT OBJECTS.

12:50.981 --> 12:53.063
I MEAN, THAT IS
HOW YOU AND YOUR KIND

12:53.063 --> 12:54.895
PREFER TO DEAL
WITH ME.

12:54.895 --> 12:57.858
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA WHAT
YOUR SPITEFUL RETALIATION

12:57.858 --> 12:59.319
DID TO MY SON?

12:59.319 --> 13:01.992
HOPEFULLY CREATE AN IRREPARABLE
RIFT BETWEEN YOU TWO.

13:01.992 --> 13:04.905
WELL, THEN, YOU'LL BE
DISAPPOINTED TO LEARN
THAT YOUR PLAN DIDN'T WORK.

13:04.905 --> 13:07.537
THE ONLY THING MEETING
HIS FATHER ACCOMPLISHED

13:07.537 --> 13:09.749
WAS TO DESTROY PATRICK.

13:09.749 --> 13:11.751
[ CHUCKLES ]
I'M SORRY.

13:11.751 --> 13:14.965
YOU EXPECT ME TO FEEL GUILTY FOR
HELPING PATRICK FIND HIS FATHER?

13:14.965 --> 13:18.048
JIMMY BRENNAN
WAS A HORRIBLE, VIOLENT MAN.

13:18.048 --> 13:21.131
AND PATRICK LEARNED
THAT HE WAS BORN

13:21.131 --> 13:23.723
FROM AN UNSPEAKABLE
CIRCUMSTANCE.

13:26.096 --> 13:28.188
I HID THE TRUTH
TO PROTECT MY SON,

13:28.188 --> 13:31.311
AND NOW, BECAUSE OF YOUR
CHILDISH, MYOPIC GAMES,

13:31.311 --> 13:33.643
PATRICK THINKS
HE'S UNWORTHY OF LOVE.

13:36.236 --> 13:37.898
I DIDN'T KNOW.

13:37.898 --> 13:39.649
AND IN YOUR ARROGANCE,
YOU DIDN'T CARE.

13:40.901 --> 13:42.782
MY SON IS
ON THE PRECIPICE.

13:42.782 --> 13:44.364
HIS LIFE IS AT RISK,

13:44.364 --> 13:48.408
AND THE BLAME RESTS SQUARELY ON
YOUR NARROW SHOULDERS, MR. ROSS.

13:52.252 --> 13:54.454
Stevie: I'M NOT SURE
HOW MUCH LONGER I'LL BE.

13:54.454 --> 13:57.217
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
 COME ON IN.
IT'S OPEN.

13:58.588 --> 14:00.090
RIGHT.

14:00.090 --> 14:02.883
NO MATTER WHAT I DECIDE TO DO
WITH GRAYSON MANOR,

14:02.883 --> 14:06.096
I'M PREPARED TO FORCE
AN EVICTION.

14:06.096 --> 14:07.467
UH-HUH.

14:09.970 --> 14:11.641
I'LL CALL YOU BACK.

14:11.641 --> 14:14.644
I GOT A CALL
FROM MY REALTOR TODAY.

14:15.685 --> 14:18.188
SEEMS THE HOUSE I WAS ABOUT TO
LOSE IS NOW MINE IF I WANT IT.

14:18.188 --> 14:20.110
THAT'S WONDERFUL.

14:20.110 --> 14:22.943
I ASKED WHAT MADE THE OWNERS
CHANGE THEIR MINDS, AND...

14:22.943 --> 14:24.364
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:24.364 --> 14:27.157
...HE SAID THEY'D RECEIVED
AN E-MAIL ON MY BEHALF

14:27.157 --> 14:29.199
FROM A TOP ATTORNEY --

14:29.199 --> 14:34.584
ONE WHO TALKED ABOUT HOW MY KID
AND I DESERVE MY DREAM HOME

14:34.584 --> 14:37.127
AFTER THE DIFFICULT LIFE
THAT I'VE HAD.

14:37.127 --> 14:39.669
I WANTED TO HELP.
 WHY?

14:39.669 --> 14:41.501
I MEAN, IF MY DAD
SENT YOU THIS STUFF,

14:41.501 --> 14:43.843
THEN YOU KNEW THAT WE WERE
ON HARD TIMES BEFORE.

14:43.843 --> 14:45.345
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

14:46.346 --> 14:48.178
PLEASE.

14:49.179 --> 14:50.931
LET ME JUST
DO THIS FOR YOU.

14:50.931 --> 14:54.354
YOU KNOW WHAT MY LAST MEMORY
OF THE WOMAN WHO RAISED ME IS?

14:55.515 --> 14:56.937
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:56.937 --> 14:59.229
[ Chuckling ] THE GIANT
BREAKFAST THAT SHE MADE ME.

14:59.229 --> 15:00.941
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:00.941 --> 15:04.654
IT WAS EGGS AND BACON,
PANCAKES.

15:06.866 --> 15:08.698
AND ICE CREAM.

15:10.200 --> 15:11.531
COULD NEVER
FIGURE OUT WHY

15:11.531 --> 15:15.585
UNTIL MY DAD TOLD ME
THAT SHE'D LEFT US.

15:15.585 --> 15:17.337
I'M NOT DOING THIS
OUT OF GUILT.

15:17.337 --> 15:20.000
[ Chuckling ] COME ON.
HOW COULD YOU NOT BE?

15:20.000 --> 15:23.303
UNLESS YOU REALLY ARE A GRAYSON,
SINCE I KNOW THEY NEVER FEEL IT.

15:25.255 --> 15:27.677
I AM NOTHING LIKE THEM.

15:35.725 --> 15:39.109
I'M SORRY YOU FEEL
THAT WAY.

15:52.622 --> 15:54.624
[ RAPID THUDDING ]

16:00.170 --> 16:04.174
I KNOW, UH, YOU'VE GOT A LONG
HISTORY OF POPPING BY MY PLACE,

16:04.174 --> 16:06.386
SO I DECIDED
I'D RETURN THE FAVOR.

16:06.386 --> 16:09.139
BESIDES, KNEW IT WAS
THE ONLY WAY YOU'D SEE ME.

16:09.139 --> 16:11.221
YOU SHOULDN'T
BE HERE, NOLAN.

16:11.221 --> 16:12.802
LOOK.
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

16:12.802 --> 16:15.935
I KNOW WE HAVE BEEN
THROUGH THE RINGER,

16:15.935 --> 16:19.059
BUT, UH,
I HAD NO IDEA

16:19.059 --> 16:21.151
WHO YOUR FATHER WAS
WHEN I DROPPED THAT BOMB.

16:21.151 --> 16:23.153
SO, IF YOU DID KNOW,
THAT WOULD'VE STOPPED YOU?

16:23.153 --> 16:25.315
YEAH...
PATRICK, IT WOULD HAVE.

16:25.315 --> 16:27.987
BUT I'M STARTING
TO WONDER WHAT,

16:27.987 --> 16:30.990
IF ANYTHING,
WILL STOP YOU.

16:31.991 --> 16:34.414
I READ ABOUT JIMMY'S
DEATH. I DON'T KNOW,
SHOULD WE CALL IT A MURDER?

16:34.414 --> 16:36.116
THEY RULED THAT
AN ACCIDENT.
 I KNOW,

16:36.116 --> 16:39.209
WHICH IS FAST BECOMING A
EUPHEMISM FOR "PATRICK DID IT."

16:39.209 --> 16:42.212
SO, LET ME ASK YOU --
HOW MANY PEOPLE DID YOU KILL

16:42.212 --> 16:45.045
BEFORE YOU CAME TO THE HAMPTONS?
'CAUSE MY GUESS IS ZERO.

16:45.045 --> 16:47.387
DON'T STAND THERE AND
ACT SO INNOCENT, NOLAN.
WE BOTH KNOW YOU'RE NOT.

16:47.387 --> 16:49.299
I DON'T HAVE BLOOD
ON MY HANDS.

16:50.300 --> 16:52.342
WAIT, SO DOES VICTORIA
PICK THE VICTIMS,

16:52.342 --> 16:54.434
OR ARE YOU JUST SCORING POINTS
WITH MOMMY?

16:54.434 --> 16:56.896
YOU GOT NO IDEA WHAT SHE'S BEEN
THROUGH, SO STOP ATTACKING HER.

16:56.896 --> 16:59.059
OR WHAT?
I'LL HAVE AN ACCIDENT NEXT?

17:01.851 --> 17:03.773
YOU'VE TOTALLY CHANGED.

17:05.194 --> 17:06.445
YOU DON'T EVEN SEE IT.

17:08.198 --> 17:10.569
YOU REALLY THINK YOU KNOW ME,
DON'T YOU?

17:12.531 --> 17:14.114
YOU DON'T.

17:15.915 --> 17:17.707
I KNOW YOU USED
TO BE AN ARTIST.

17:17.707 --> 17:20.039
YEAH, WELL...
 AND I KNOW YOU'VE GOT
A BOOTH AT THE ART WALK

17:20.039 --> 17:22.252
THAT'S CURRENTLY
SITTING EMPTY,

17:22.252 --> 17:25.425
AND I KNOW
THAT STEFANO LEONE

17:25.425 --> 17:27.507
WILL BE DISAPPOINTED.

17:27.507 --> 17:29.509
STEFANO LEONE'S
GONNA BE THERE?

17:29.509 --> 17:31.341
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

17:31.341 --> 17:34.434
I SET IT UP
BACK WHEN WE WERE DATING.

17:34.434 --> 17:38.848
I, UH, WANTED IT
TO BE A SURPRISE.

17:38.848 --> 17:40.730
PATRICK...

17:40.730 --> 17:44.734
I WANTED GOOD THINGS
FOR YOU, AND [CHUCKLES]

17:44.734 --> 17:46.816
CALL ME CRAZY...

17:46.816 --> 17:49.028
MM, I STILL DO.

17:49.028 --> 17:51.651
BUT SINCE I FORGOT
THAT YOU CAN'T DO ANYTHING

17:51.651 --> 17:53.743
THAT VICTORIA
DOESN'T SANCTION,

17:53.743 --> 17:57.747
I WILL SEND STEFANO
YOUR REGRETS.

18:05.375 --> 18:06.876
[ GASPS, COUGHS ]

18:06.876 --> 18:08.548
THAT'S NOT GONNA WORK!

18:08.548 --> 18:11.171
ONLY BY STRIPPING AWAY THE BODY
CAN WE THEN FOCUS ON YOUR MIND,

18:11.171 --> 18:12.762
AND BY SHEDDING THAT,
YOUR SOUL.

18:12.762 --> 18:14.174
YOU'LL NEVER BE TAKEDA.

18:14.174 --> 18:15.595
YOU THINK I WANT
TO BE HERE?

18:15.595 --> 18:17.016
I ONLY CAME BACK
BECAUSE YOU DESTROYED US,

18:17.016 --> 18:18.598
AND I WON'T LET THAT BE
FOR NOTHING.

18:18.598 --> 18:20.600
I DIDN'T ASK
FOR YOUR HELP.
 GOD.
YOU'RE UNGRATEFUL.

18:20.600 --> 18:22.222
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHO YOUR ALLIES ARE ANYMORE.

18:22.222 --> 18:24.644
BUT I KNOW
WHO MY ENEMIES ARE.
 WHO, THE GRAYSONS?

18:24.644 --> 18:26.776
THEN WHY DIDN'T
YOUR BLACKOUTS HARM THEM?

18:26.776 --> 18:28.688
NO, INSTEAD,
YOU WENT AFTER NOLAN AND ME.

18:28.688 --> 18:30.150
YOU'RE MISDIRECTING
YOUR ANGER.

18:30.150 --> 18:32.652
I THINK THE PERSON YOU'RE
TRULY ANGRY AT IS YOURSELF,

18:32.652 --> 18:34.033
BUT YOU WON'T ADMIT IT.

18:34.033 --> 18:36.075
[ PANTING ]
GO TO HELL.

18:41.791 --> 18:43.002
[ HEART BEATING ]

18:48.798 --> 18:50.590
[ HEART BEATING FASTER ]

18:57.807 --> 18:59.559
[ GASPING ]

19:03.183 --> 19:04.854
EMILY?

19:09.028 --> 19:10.610
MY FATHER...

19:12.151 --> 19:14.153
HE'S TO BLAME
FOR EVERYTHING.

19:18.988 --> 19:21.040
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

19:21.040 --> 19:23.042
[ JAZZ MUSIC PLAYS ]

19:23.042 --> 19:24.664
PAUL CHARNEY.

19:24.664 --> 19:27.247
OR SHOULD I SAY
"YOUR HONOR" NOW?

19:27.247 --> 19:29.879
ENJOYING A RESPITE
BEFORE THE FALL TERM?

19:29.879 --> 19:32.842
TO BE HONEST, STEVIE, I JUST
HEARD SOME DISTURBING NEWS.

19:32.842 --> 19:34.294
PAUL AND I
WERE DISCUSSING

19:34.294 --> 19:35.885
YOUR PLANS
TO LEVEL GRAYSON MANOR.

19:35.885 --> 19:38.798
I'VE ACTUALLY
CHANGED MY MIND.

19:38.798 --> 19:41.010
NOW I'M THINKING
IT COULD BE PUT TO BETTER USE

19:41.010 --> 19:42.512
AS A HALFWAY HOUSE.

19:44.264 --> 19:46.396
THE MANOR IS
AN ARCHITECTURAL TREASURE.

19:46.396 --> 19:47.897
AND PAUL
IS THE CHAIRPERSON

19:47.897 --> 19:50.610
OF THE SOUTH HAMPTON
HISTORICAL COMMISSION.

19:50.610 --> 19:52.111
HE WANTS TO SEE TO IT
THAT IT'S PROTECTED

19:52.111 --> 19:53.613
BY NATIONAL
LANDMARK LAWS.

19:53.613 --> 19:56.075
WHICH MEANS IT CAN'T BE USED
AS A TREATMENT CENTER

19:56.075 --> 19:57.577
OR ANYTHING ELSE.

19:57.577 --> 20:01.531
A LANDMARK NEEDS TO MEET
HALF A DOZEN HISTORICAL CRITERIA

20:01.531 --> 20:03.413
TO BE REGISTERED.

20:03.413 --> 20:06.536
I HARDLY THINK
GRAYSON MANOR QUALIFIES,

20:06.536 --> 20:09.959
UNLESS THERE'S A VALUE IN
THE LEGACY OF TABLOID SCANDALS.

20:09.959 --> 20:11.421
CAREFUL, STEVIE.

20:11.421 --> 20:13.673
YOU'RE NO STRANGER
TO SCANDAL, EITHER.

20:13.673 --> 20:14.924
SEE YOU IN COURT.

20:16.836 --> 20:19.719
WELL, IT SEEMS IT'S NOT JUST ME
YOU'LL BE FIGHTING WITH.

20:19.719 --> 20:22.302
IT'S FUNNY. I WOULDN'T THINK
YOU'D NEED SO MUCH HELP.

20:26.556 --> 20:29.228
[ EMILY SNIFFLES ]

20:29.228 --> 20:31.981
ARE YOU READY
TO TALK?

20:31.981 --> 20:33.613
[ SNIFFLES ]

20:33.613 --> 20:35.615
UNTIE ME, PLEASE.

20:37.657 --> 20:39.659
[ SIGHS ]

20:46.075 --> 20:47.707
[ GRUNTS ]

20:47.707 --> 20:49.539
[ SIGHS ]

20:55.335 --> 20:56.926
[ SIGHS ]

20:58.678 --> 21:00.680
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

21:02.051 --> 21:04.474
IT WAS MY FATHER
ALL ALONG.

21:07.056 --> 21:09.649
THAT'S WHY YOU DEFACED
THE CARVING HE MADE FOR YOU.

21:13.693 --> 21:16.526
[ SIGHS ]
OR WAS IT SOMETHING MORE?

21:18.658 --> 21:21.451
HE CARVED IT THE MORNING
HE WAS TAKEN.

21:23.072 --> 21:24.744
WHY THAT DAY?

21:25.995 --> 21:28.167
I DON'T KNOW.

21:30.670 --> 21:33.333
I THINK I WAS IN TROUBLE
FOR SOMETHING.

21:33.333 --> 21:35.335
ARE YOU CERTAIN
THAT IT WAS YOUR FATHER?

21:35.335 --> 21:37.176
TRY AND REMEMBER,
EMILY.

21:45.094 --> 21:47.727
Emily: IT WAS THE NIGHT
BEFORE HE WAS TAKEN.

21:47.727 --> 21:49.639
VICTORIA.

21:51.601 --> 21:55.935
SHE WAS SAYING SHE WANTED TO
RUN AWAY WITH HIM.

21:55.935 --> 21:58.698
HE DIDN'T SEE ME,
BUT SHE SAW ME IN THE SHADOWS.

21:58.698 --> 22:01.320
SHE GAVE ME THIS LOOK.

22:01.320 --> 22:02.992
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

22:04.864 --> 22:07.707
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

22:07.707 --> 22:09.499
YOU ALREADY
TOLD ME ALL THIS.

22:09.499 --> 22:11.581
BE BRAVE ENOUGH
TO GO DEEPER.

22:11.581 --> 22:13.373
[ SIGHS ]

22:16.796 --> 22:19.088
I KNEW SHE COULDN'T
BE TRUSTED.

22:19.088 --> 22:21.090
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

22:24.514 --> 22:27.176
I JUST WANTED
TO MAKE SURE HE WAS OKAY.

22:31.350 --> 22:32.351
[ GASPS ]

22:35.475 --> 22:37.106
DAVID.

22:37.106 --> 22:39.068
DAVID!
 GET OUT!

22:41.280 --> 22:43.322
[ Crying ] NO!
 AMANDA, STOP!

22:43.322 --> 22:44.904
NO, STOP!
 STOP! STOP!

22:44.904 --> 22:47.747
HEY. HEY.
 LET ME GO!
YOU YELLED AT ME!

22:47.747 --> 22:50.329
WHAT'S SHE DOING HERE?
I DON'T LIKE HER! SHE HATES ME!

22:50.329 --> 22:52.041
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

22:52.041 --> 22:53.372
YOU DON'T
EVEN KNOW HER YET.

22:53.372 --> 22:55.545
NO, TELL HER
TO GO AWAY NOW!

22:55.545 --> 22:56.626
I'M NOT GONNA
DO THAT, AMANDA.

22:56.626 --> 22:57.497
I LOVE HER,
AND YOU WILL, TOO.

22:57.497 --> 22:59.338
NO,
SHE'S NOT MY MOM.

22:59.338 --> 23:02.552
HEY. HEY.
YOUR MOM IS GONE.

23:02.552 --> 23:05.134
YOU HAVE TO ACCEPT
VICTORIA,

23:05.134 --> 23:07.557
BECAUSE
WE ARE GONNA BE A FAMILY.

23:07.557 --> 23:10.680
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

23:10.680 --> 23:12.852
[ Voice breaking ]
HE GOT HIS WISH.

23:14.934 --> 23:17.567
I'M A GRAYSON NOW.

23:18.648 --> 23:20.189
EMILY.

23:22.572 --> 23:24.484
WHY DIDN'T HE
LISTEN TO ME?

23:26.325 --> 23:27.947
WHY?

23:29.158 --> 23:31.160
EVERYTHING COULD'VE
BEEN DIFFERENT.

23:33.032 --> 23:35.455
[ WHIMPERS, SNIFFLES ]
EVERYTHING COULD'VE BEEN...

23:35.455 --> 23:37.246
IT'S OKAY.

23:47.386 --> 23:48.678
PATRICK?

23:48.678 --> 23:50.890
HI.

23:50.890 --> 23:53.723
WELL, AFTER THIS MORNING,
I DIDN'T THINK YOU WOULD COME.

23:53.723 --> 23:56.185
WELL, I, YOU KNOW, FIGURED
FORCING MYSELF OUT

23:56.185 --> 23:58.858
MIGHT HELP ME SHAKE WHATEVER
IT IS I'M FEELING, SO...

23:58.858 --> 24:01.360
IT'S IMPORTANT THAT YOU STOP
TORTURING YOURSELF

24:01.360 --> 24:03.613
ABOUT THE PAST AND START LIVING
IN THE PRESENT...

24:04.904 --> 24:07.657
...BECAUSE THERE ARE ALWAYS
PROBLEMS TO BE DEALT WITH.

24:09.529 --> 24:11.120
SOMETHING WRONG?

24:11.120 --> 24:13.623
OH, NOTHING THAT YOU NEED
TO WORRY ABOUT.

24:13.623 --> 24:16.285
LET'S FOCUS ON PUTTING
YOUR ARTWORK UP, YEAH?

24:17.787 --> 24:20.379
MOM, WHY DON'T YOU JUST
TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON?

24:25.214 --> 24:27.216
STEVIE GRAYSON.

24:28.588 --> 24:30.049
SHE'S PROVING
TO BE MORE TENACIOUS

24:30.049 --> 24:31.851
AT THE PURSUIT
OF OUR HOME THAN I THOUGHT.

24:31.851 --> 24:33.643
YOU GOT THE CITY COUNCIL
ON YOUR SIDE, RIGHT?

24:33.643 --> 24:36.225
WELL, THEY'RE NO MATCH
FOR HER LEGAL ACROBATICS.

24:36.225 --> 24:38.598
TO THINK THAT WHEN SHE
AND CONRAD WERE TOGETHER,

24:38.598 --> 24:41.651
SHE WAS NOTHING BUT A SOCIALITE
ENJOYING THE HIGH LIFE.

24:41.651 --> 24:43.603
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]
WHAT CHANGED HER?

24:43.603 --> 24:45.565
I DID.

24:45.565 --> 24:48.988
AFTER CONRAD LEFT HER FOR ME,
IT MUST'VE BEEN A WAKE-UP CALL.

24:48.988 --> 24:52.281
BUT IF SHE THINKS THAT I'M GOING
TO TOLERATE HER INSOLENCE,

24:52.281 --> 24:54.493
SHE'S WRONG.

24:54.493 --> 24:57.076
THERE ARE OTHER WAYS
TO DEAL WITH HER.

24:57.076 --> 24:58.668
WHAT ARE YOU
TRYING TO SAY?

24:58.668 --> 25:01.170
THAT IF I CREATED
THIS BEAST,

25:01.170 --> 25:03.082
DON'T YOU THINK
IT'S TIME I SLAY IT?

25:03.082 --> 25:05.925
MOM, I NEED TO KNOW WHAT IT IS
YOU'RE PLANNING TO DO.

25:05.925 --> 25:07.837
I WON'T GO
INTO THE DETAILS HERE.

25:07.837 --> 25:11.631
TODAY IS ABOUT YOU
AND YOUR WORK, ALL RIGHT?

25:20.439 --> 25:22.141
[ SIGHS ]

25:25.605 --> 25:28.447
I FINALLY REMEMBER
WHAT I DID DURING MY BLACKOUTS.

25:31.150 --> 25:33.242
IT'S ALL BECAUSE
OF THAT ONE MEMORY.

25:33.242 --> 25:36.656
THAT'S WHY I WAS
SABOTAGING EVERYTHING.

25:36.656 --> 25:39.248
BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T
THINK HE WAS WORTH IT.

25:41.540 --> 25:44.584
WITH EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED
WITH MY FATHER, I UNDERSTAND.

25:47.216 --> 25:49.428
YOU'RE THE ONLY PERSON
WHO KNEW HOW TO SAVE ME.

25:51.801 --> 25:53.552
I'M NOT SURE I DESERVE IT.

25:53.552 --> 25:55.384
YOU DO.

25:55.384 --> 25:57.516
AND SO DOES YOUR FATHER.

26:02.271 --> 26:04.143
THE ONLY MISTAKE
HE MADE WAS...

26:06.065 --> 26:08.147
...FALLING
FOR THE WRONG WOMAN.

26:15.284 --> 26:17.286
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

26:17.286 --> 26:21.080
WHICH MEANS I STILL
NEED TO CLEAR HIS NAME.

26:21.080 --> 26:24.163
NOW, THAT'S
THE EMILY I KNOW.

26:27.707 --> 26:29.879
NOW, YOU FINISH
WHAT YOU STARTED.

26:29.879 --> 26:32.301
YOU MAKE THEM PAY
FOR WHAT THEY'VE DONE.

26:53.152 --> 26:55.154
[ SIGHS ]

27:10.750 --> 27:13.302
THE BRUSH STROKES
ARE A BIT HEAVY,

27:13.302 --> 27:15.845
BUT I THINK MAYBE
THAT WAS INTENTIONAL.

27:15.845 --> 27:19.428
UH, MR. LEONE.
IT'S AN HONOR, SIR.

27:19.428 --> 27:22.311
AN HONOR WOULD BE
AN ANSWER TO MY QUESTION.

27:22.311 --> 27:24.223
RIGHT. UH...

27:26.565 --> 27:28.858
HONESTLY,
I WAS TRYING TO --

27:28.858 --> 27:30.649
WAS TRYING TO RAM THE PAINT
THROUGH THE CANVAS THAT DAY,

27:30.649 --> 27:33.823
WHICH NEVER REALLY LEADS
TO GOOD ART, DOES IT?

27:33.823 --> 27:35.444
BUT THE TALENT IS THERE.

27:38.077 --> 27:40.329
I UNDERSTAND
YOU RUN A GALLERY.

27:40.329 --> 27:43.282
UH, WITH MY MOTHER, YES.
I DO, YEAH.

27:43.282 --> 27:46.205
WELL, THEN,
THIS MAY NOT INTEREST YOU,

27:46.205 --> 27:49.288
BUT I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR AN
APPRENTICE IN MY TUSCAN STUDIO.

27:49.288 --> 27:52.671
THE PAY IS MINIMAL,
AND THE HOURS ARE LONG.

27:52.671 --> 27:54.213
UH, I...

27:54.213 --> 27:56.055
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

27:56.055 --> 27:58.257
UM...
 JUST CONSIDER IT.

28:14.774 --> 28:16.776
[ DOOR OPENS ]

28:18.818 --> 28:20.659
HEY.

28:20.659 --> 28:22.661
FINALLY FEEL
LIKE TALKING?

28:24.203 --> 28:26.165
YEAH.
 GOOD.

28:26.165 --> 28:27.747
COME HERE FOR A SECOND.

28:29.328 --> 28:34.043
NOW, YOU KNOW,
WE ALL MAKE MISTAKES, AMANDA.

28:34.043 --> 28:36.926
I'M SORRY THAT WE FOUGHT
AND THAT YOU GOT SCARED.

28:36.926 --> 28:39.969
I, UH, NEVER WANT
THAT FOR YOU.

28:41.841 --> 28:42.932
RIGHT.

28:46.846 --> 28:49.058
DADDY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

28:49.058 --> 28:50.349
RIGHT NOW, IT ALL LOOKS
REALLY BAD, RIGHT?

28:50.349 --> 28:51.941
YEAH.

28:51.941 --> 28:55.314
BUT YOU AND I --
WE CAN FIX ANY PROBLEM.

28:56.856 --> 28:59.658
WHEN THIS IS DONE,
IT'S GONNA BE A REMINDER

28:59.658 --> 29:03.202
THAT NO MISTAKE
IS EVER GONNA BREAK US APART.

29:03.202 --> 29:07.286
AS LONG AS YOU
NEVER FORGET I LOVE YOU.

29:11.210 --> 29:12.711
[ FOOTSTEPS ]

29:12.711 --> 29:14.213
Jack: EMILY?

29:16.085 --> 29:18.137
JACK, HEY.

29:18.137 --> 29:19.548
CAN I, UH...

29:19.548 --> 29:21.590
CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A MINUTE?

29:21.590 --> 29:23.803
OF COURSE.

29:25.764 --> 29:28.687
WHEN YOUR MOM SHOWED UP, DID
YOU GET A CHANCE TO TALK TO HER?

29:28.687 --> 29:31.190
I MEAN...HONESTLY?

29:31.190 --> 29:33.602
UM...

29:35.815 --> 29:38.237
I WISH I COULD HAVE.

29:38.237 --> 29:39.568
WHY?

29:43.362 --> 29:45.494
'CAUSE MY MOTHER
JUST CAME BACK,

29:45.494 --> 29:48.037
AND I'M NOT REALLY SURE
WHAT TO DO ABOUT IT.

29:48.037 --> 29:50.169
WHAT?

29:50.169 --> 29:52.171
YOU HAVEN'T SEEN HER
IN 20 YEARS.

29:52.171 --> 29:54.413
[ SIGHS ] ACTUALLY, I'M NOT
TALKING ABOUT THE PERSON

29:54.413 --> 29:57.466
THAT I'VE BEEN PISSED OFF
AT THIS WHOLE TIME FOR
BAILING ON ME AND DEC.

29:57.466 --> 29:59.678
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

29:59.678 --> 30:01.130
[ SIGHS ]

30:02.421 --> 30:06.055
STEVIE GRAYSON
IS MY BIOLOGICAL MOTHER.

30:08.888 --> 30:10.269
WHAT?

30:10.269 --> 30:12.771
SHE HAD AN AFFAIR WITH MY DAD,
AND SHE LEFT TOWN,

30:12.771 --> 30:14.433
HID THE PREGNANCY
FROM CONRAD,

30:14.433 --> 30:16.815
THEN MY DAD AND MOM
RAISED ME AS THEIR OWN.

30:16.815 --> 30:18.697
STEVIE GRAYSON?

30:20.609 --> 30:21.610
ARE YOU SURE?

30:24.703 --> 30:26.365
WHAT ELSE DID SHE SAY?

30:28.287 --> 30:32.081
JUST, YOU KNOW, THAT [SIGHS]
IT WAS HARD TO LET ME GO,

30:32.081 --> 30:34.583
BUT I-I CAN TELL THAT
SHE'S HOLDING SOMETHING BACK.

30:34.583 --> 30:36.415
AND IF SHE'S
THIS CLOSED OFF ALREADY,

30:36.415 --> 30:38.457
I DON'T SEE THE POINT
IN MAKING AN EFFORT.

30:38.457 --> 30:40.669
WELL,
IF THIS IS TRUE...

30:42.882 --> 30:45.594
...SHE'S THE ONLY PARENT
YOU'VE GOT.

30:45.594 --> 30:49.098
AND, YEAH, SHE MADE
A MISTAKE YEARS AGO, BUT...

30:51.350 --> 30:53.642
...MAYBE YOU SHOULD
GIVE HER A CHANCE.

30:55.434 --> 30:58.607
JUST PLEASE BE CAREFUL.

30:59.979 --> 31:01.981
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

31:15.584 --> 31:17.126
AND, JACK...

31:19.088 --> 31:22.091
...THANKS FOR GIVING ME
A CHANCE, TOO.

31:23.092 --> 31:24.503
IT MEANS A LOT.

31:34.103 --> 31:35.644
[ SIGHS ]

31:38.647 --> 31:41.280
[ SIGHS ]

31:44.523 --> 31:48.117
Patrick: MOM, THIS IS REALLY
HARD FOR ME TO SAY.

31:48.117 --> 31:50.659
BUT, UH...

31:50.659 --> 31:54.243
YOU KNOW THAT
WHEN YOU HURT, I HURT, TOO.

31:55.834 --> 31:58.297
AND THE PROBLEM IS,
WHEN SOMEONE HURTS YOU...

32:00.299 --> 32:02.671
...I BECOME SOMEONE
I BARELY RECOGNIZE,

32:02.671 --> 32:05.094
SOMEONE WHO WILL...

32:05.094 --> 32:08.257
STRIKE OUT TO PROTECT
THE ONE PERSON I VALUE MOST.

32:08.257 --> 32:11.850
AND I KNOW NOW WHERE
THAT DARKNESS COMES FROM.

32:11.850 --> 32:14.053
IT COMES FROM MY FATHER.

32:14.053 --> 32:17.516
I FEEL LIKE IF I STAY HERE,
OTHERS WILL SUFFER, TOO.

32:20.019 --> 32:21.610
I'VE BEEN GIVEN
AN OPPORTUNITY,

32:21.610 --> 32:24.693
ONE THAT I THINK
WILL MAKE YOU PROUD OF ME.

32:26.115 --> 32:28.657
BUT IT MEANS
I HAVE TO LEAVE HERE.

32:28.657 --> 32:31.070
AND I HATE DOING THIS THE WAY
THAT I'M DOING IT,

32:31.070 --> 32:34.873
BUT I CAN'T LOOK
IN YOUR EYES.

32:34.873 --> 32:38.417
IF I DID,
I WOULD WAVER.

32:38.417 --> 32:40.879
I REALLY HOPE
YOU UNDERSTAND.

32:44.843 --> 32:48.467
Goodbye, Mom.
I will always love you.

33:02.101 --> 33:03.812
HAVE YOU HEARD THE NEWS?

33:03.812 --> 33:06.695
PASCAL LeMARCHAL
IS ON HIS WAY FROM PARIS.

33:06.695 --> 33:09.278
OH, I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE SUCH A FAN.

33:09.278 --> 33:12.571
WELL, I'M NOT, REALLY, BUT HE'S
ONE OF THE BIGGEST MEDIA MOGULS

33:12.571 --> 33:15.664
IN THE WORLD, AND HE'LL BE
IN THESE OFFICES TOMORROW.

33:15.664 --> 33:17.746
RIGHT ON SCHEDULE.

33:19.248 --> 33:21.580
THAT'S WHY YOU CHALLENGED
MARGAUX'S AUTHORITY.

33:21.580 --> 33:23.582
YOU KNEW SHE'D HAVE TO
GO TO THE BOARD.

33:23.582 --> 33:25.544
WHICH MEANT
RUNNING HOME TO PAPA,

33:25.544 --> 33:27.756
AND I KNEW HE COULDN'T
RESIST ENGAGING ME

33:27.756 --> 33:29.508
ON HIS
DAUGHTER'S BEHALF.

33:29.508 --> 33:31.800
BUT WHY DO YOU WANT
MR. LeMARCHAL HERE?

33:31.800 --> 33:35.634
OH, WELL, CHARLOTTE,
I COULD TELL YOU,

33:35.634 --> 33:38.977
OR, IF YOU WANT TO SEE
 HOW THE BUSINESS OF POWER WORKS,

33:38.977 --> 33:41.940
YOU COULD TAKE
A RINGSIDE SEAT.

33:41.940 --> 33:43.642
SIGN ME UP.

33:50.779 --> 33:52.281
JACK.

33:54.032 --> 33:55.704
THE ONLY TIME I'VE MISSED OUT
ON MY KID'S LIFE

33:55.704 --> 33:56.865
IS WHEN THINGS WERE TRULY
MESSED UP,

33:56.865 --> 33:58.327
SO WHATEVER IT WAS
THAT MADE YOU STAY AWAY,

33:58.327 --> 34:00.079
IT MUST'VE BEEN BAD, BUT...

34:01.500 --> 34:04.833
...I GUESS I JUST WANTED
TO MAKE SURE IT WASN'T
BECAUSE OF ME OR MY DAD.

34:04.833 --> 34:07.086
IT WASN'T.

34:07.086 --> 34:08.757
[ SIGHS ]

34:15.434 --> 34:17.436
[ SIGHS ]

34:21.059 --> 34:24.233
I WAS ACTUALLY TRYING TO
PROTECT YOU FROM WHO I WAS THEN.

34:32.531 --> 34:34.533
[ SIGHS ]

34:36.455 --> 34:38.617
WHEN I LIVED HERE,

34:38.617 --> 34:42.791
I COULDN'T EXIST
WITHOUT A DRINK IN MY HAND,

34:42.791 --> 34:47.335
HENCE MY TIME AT YOUR BAR
AND WITH YOUR FATHER.

34:47.335 --> 34:52.971
BUT NOW I'M SOBER,
COMING UP ON 20 YEARS.

34:56.094 --> 34:57.846
[ SIGHS ]

35:01.019 --> 35:03.602
[ SIGHS ]

35:03.602 --> 35:05.524
I WAS, UM...

35:06.565 --> 35:08.817
I WAS IN REHAB
FOR THE FIRST TIME

35:08.817 --> 35:10.729
WHEN I FOUND OUT
I WAS PREGNANT.

35:12.611 --> 35:15.234
BUT AFTER I HAD YOU,
I REALIZED...

35:16.735 --> 35:20.289
...I COULDN'T BE A DECENT
MOTHER UNTIL I LEARNED HOW
TO TAKE CARE OF MYSELF,

35:20.289 --> 35:24.793
WHICH TOOK LONGER
THAN I EXPECTED.

35:26.745 --> 35:28.377
IT WAS 30 YEARS.

35:28.377 --> 35:29.748
I KNOW.

35:29.748 --> 35:34.633
THE HAMPTONS ARE
FULL OF TRIGGERS FOR ME,

35:34.633 --> 35:37.716
THE GREATEST
BEING CONRAD AND VICTORIA.

35:37.716 --> 35:40.018
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

35:40.018 --> 35:43.852
WELL...
THAT, I CAN UNDERSTAND.

35:45.434 --> 35:47.606
BUT STILL, WHY NOW?

35:47.606 --> 35:49.978
I WAS READY
TO FACE THEM.

35:51.650 --> 35:53.272
AND YOU.

36:00.078 --> 36:02.160
THEN HOW ABOUT THIS?

36:03.742 --> 36:07.746
HOW ABOUT YOU COME OVER
TO MY HOUSE TOMORROW,

36:07.746 --> 36:10.339
OFFICIALLY
MEET YOUR GRANDSON?

36:10.339 --> 36:12.130
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:14.753 --> 36:16.925
[ Voice breaking ]
I WOULD LIKE NOTHING MORE.

36:18.557 --> 36:19.928
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

36:28.857 --> 36:32.771
I THOUGHT BRUNELLO
APPROPRIATE

36:32.771 --> 36:37.526
TO...HONOR THE NEXT CHAPTER
OF PATRICK'S LIFE.

36:39.238 --> 36:42.661
PLEASE THANK STEFANO AGAIN FOR
AFFORDING HIM THE OPPORTUNITY.

36:44.823 --> 36:47.165
YOU WERE THE ONE THAT MADE HIM
AN OFFER HE COULDN'T REFUSE,

36:47.165 --> 36:48.877
BUT...

36:48.877 --> 36:51.880
IN TRUTH,
EVEN WITHOUT THE MONEY,

36:51.880 --> 36:54.253
HE THINKS
YOUR BOY HAS TALENT.

36:55.334 --> 36:57.926
OF COURSE HE DOES.

36:57.926 --> 37:01.890
MAYBE NOW, PATRICK CAN RID HIS
HEART OF ALL THE HURT AND HATRED

37:01.890 --> 37:04.893
THAT CLOUDED IT
DURING HIS TIME HERE.

37:07.105 --> 37:09.107
YOUR PLAN WORKED,
VICTORIA.

37:10.809 --> 37:12.230
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

37:14.152 --> 37:17.356
IT SICKENS ME THAT THE ONLY WAY
TO SAVE PATRICK

37:17.356 --> 37:19.778
WAS TO LET HIM THINK
I WAS A MONSTER

37:19.778 --> 37:22.120
WHO WANTED
STEVIE GRAYSON DEAD.

37:23.201 --> 37:25.033
WHAT?
NO SNAPPY REJOINDER?

37:25.033 --> 37:26.825
NONE NEEDED.

37:26.825 --> 37:30.248
YOU LET ME HELP
BREAK YOUR HEART.

37:31.370 --> 37:33.752
DON'T TELL ME YOURS
DOESN'T HURT, TOO.

37:36.335 --> 37:37.836
TO PATRICK.

37:41.800 --> 37:43.802
TO MY SON.

37:53.151 --> 37:56.274
I ASSUME YOU HAVE
INFORMATION ON MY WIFE.

37:56.274 --> 37:59.528
IT WASN'T AS DIFFICULT TO TRACK
AS YOU LED ME TO BELIEVE.

37:59.528 --> 38:02.571
WAS SHE
WITH MY FATHER?

38:02.571 --> 38:04.743
I THINK YOU'RE TESTING
THE WRONG THEORY.

38:04.743 --> 38:07.366
SHE ACTUALLY BROKE INTO HIS ROOM
AT THE SOUTHFORK.

38:07.366 --> 38:09.708
WHY?
 I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HER PLAN WAS.

38:09.708 --> 38:11.830
ABOUT 30 SECONDS LATER,
SOME GUY CAME IN AFTER HER.

38:11.830 --> 38:13.792
I HAD TO DUCK BEHIND A WALL
SO HE DIDN'T SEE ME.

38:13.792 --> 38:15.544
THE NEXT THING I KNOW,
THEY'RE GONE.

38:15.544 --> 38:17.716
SO YOU LOST THEM?

38:17.716 --> 38:20.629
I CAME OUT THE SERVICE
ENTRANCE AND CAUGHT A
PLATE AS HE DROVE OFF.

38:20.629 --> 38:23.131
FED THE SPECS TO A COUPLE
BUDDIES IN THE FORCE,

38:23.131 --> 38:25.804
AND A COUPLE HOURS LATER,
THEY FOUND HIS CAR.

38:35.103 --> 38:36.985
YOU'VE SEEN HIM
BEFORE.

38:36.985 --> 38:38.857
[ SIGHS ]

38:38.857 --> 38:41.860
AND I NEVER THOUGHT I'D BE
HAPPY TO SEE HIM AGAIN.

38:46.945 --> 38:49.788
I'M GLAD
IT WORKED OUT.

38:49.788 --> 38:54.082
I FINALLY, UH,
UNDERSTAND WHY SHE WAS SCARED.

38:54.082 --> 38:57.956
TURNS OUT
SHE'S A RECOVERING ALCOHOLIC.

38:57.956 --> 39:01.299
THE GRAYSONS AREN'T
EXACTLY HER FAVORITE PEOPLE.

39:01.299 --> 39:03.512
WELL, IT'S GOOD
THAT SHE OPENED UP.

39:03.512 --> 39:05.464
[ Baby crying ]

39:05.464 --> 39:06.805
AH.

39:06.805 --> 39:09.227
DUTY CALLS.

39:09.227 --> 39:12.060
GOOD NIGHT, EMILY.

39:12.060 --> 39:13.682
GOOD NIGHT.

39:15.564 --> 39:17.235
[ SIGHS ]

39:17.235 --> 39:19.027
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

39:20.278 --> 39:21.279
HEY.

39:21.279 --> 39:22.781
HEY.

39:22.781 --> 39:24.573
SPRUCING UP
THE COTTAGE?

39:24.573 --> 39:26.034
THAT'S A GOOD SIGN.

39:26.034 --> 39:27.946
HOW YOU FEELING?

39:27.946 --> 39:29.948
BETTER.
 YEAH?

39:29.948 --> 39:33.251
YEAH, I THINK I FINALLY HAVE
A HANDLE ON ALL THIS.

39:33.251 --> 39:36.124
NOW THAT YOU'VE SENT
YOUR DEMONS PACKING,

39:36.124 --> 39:37.956
IS DANNY NEXT?

39:39.167 --> 39:41.800
NOT UNTIL I KNOW
WHAT MY NEXT STEP IS,

39:41.800 --> 39:45.133
BUT IT WILL BE GOOD TO HAVE
A REFUGE FROM GRAYSON MANOR.

39:47.215 --> 39:49.558
AND...

39:49.558 --> 39:54.563
CONSIDER THIS
A HOUSE RE-WARMING.

39:56.475 --> 39:59.147
AND...

39:59.147 --> 40:02.190
ONLY YOUR TOUCH
CAN OPEN IT.
 [ LOCK WHIRS, CLICKS ]

40:04.863 --> 40:06.364
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

40:07.486 --> 40:09.488
THANK YOU, NOLAN...

40:11.830 --> 40:14.493
...FOR THIS...

40:14.493 --> 40:16.915
AND FOR SENDING
AIDEN TODAY.

40:18.126 --> 40:21.039
[ SIGHS ]
ALMOST LOST EVERYTHING.

40:21.039 --> 40:23.091
YEAH, I HOPED
HE'D COME THROUGH FOR YOU.

40:24.963 --> 40:28.006
SO, I THINK THIS CALLS
FOR A TOAST.

40:28.006 --> 40:30.599
I'M THINKING...
GIN MARTINIS?

40:32.971 --> 40:34.432
GIN MARTINIS?

40:34.432 --> 40:36.475
Jack: TURNS OUT
 SHE'S A RECOVERING ALCOHOLIC.

40:36.475 --> 40:38.396
David:
 GIN ON HER BREATH.

40:47.065 --> 40:49.868
I DON'T GET MANY VISITORS,
 BUT WHEN I DO,

40:49.868 --> 40:52.911
IT GIVES ME A MOMENT OF HOPE
 WITHIN THE STRUGGLE.

40:55.203 --> 40:58.837
BECAUSE I THINK MAYBE YOU'LL
 WALK THROUGH THAT DOOR

40:58.837 --> 41:00.839
HAVING FORGIVEN ME.

41:00.839 --> 41:02.841
I HAD THAT HOPE TODAY.

41:03.922 --> 41:05.924
[ DOOR BUZZES ]

41:14.723 --> 41:16.555
Stevie:
MR. CLARKE.

41:16.555 --> 41:19.648
I'M A LAWYER,
AND I'M INTERESTED IN YOUR CASE.

41:19.648 --> 41:22.100
I WANTED TO BELIEVE HER,

41:22.100 --> 41:24.693
BUT THAT'S WHEN I NOTICED
 THE GIN ON HER BREATH.

41:24.693 --> 41:26.525
A FEW DAYS LATER,
 I FOUND OUT

41:26.525 --> 41:29.237
THAT SHE'D BEEN DISBARRED
 FOR DRINKING.

41:29.237 --> 41:32.951
BUT I STILL CHERISH THE ONE
 MOMENT OF HOPE I HAD THAT DAY,

41:32.951 --> 41:35.874
BECAUSE THAT HOPE
 IS YOU, AMANDA.

41:35.874 --> 41:37.916
IT ALWAYS IS.

41:37.916 --> 41:40.168
CIN-CIN.
[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

41:42.040 --> 41:43.962
EMS?

41:43.962 --> 41:45.714
WHAT'S WRONG?

41:46.835 --> 41:48.757
A LAWYER DISBARRED.

41:50.759 --> 41:54.763
I THINK STEVIE GRAYSON
VISITED MY FATHER IN PRISON.

41:54.763 --> 41:56.184
[ SIGHS ]

41:56.184 --> 41:58.807
WHAT DO YOU THINK
SHE WANTED?

41:58.807 --> 42:01.439
I DON'T KNOW.

42:01.439 --> 42:03.812
BUT SHE CAME HERE
WITH SECRETS.

42:05.734 --> 42:07.736
I'M GONNA FIND OUT
EVERY SINGLE ONE.
